simple Python program that demonstrates Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts by creating a basic class and instances:
--------------------------------------------

class Dog:
    def __init__(self, name, age):
        self.name = name
        self.age = age

    def bark(self):
        print(f"{self.name} is barking!")

    def info(self):
        print(f"{self.name} is {self.age} years old.")

# Creating instances of the Dog class
dog1 = Dog("Buddy", 3)
dog2 = Dog("Charlie", 5)

# Calling methods on the instances
dog1.bark()
dog2.info()
